OL,3,CProbation chief warns 'things will go
OL,4,Cwrong' with early prison release scheme
OL,6,FIt is "inevitable that things will go
OL,7,Fwrong" when prisoners are freed early
OL,8,Fin response to the overcrowding
OL,9,Fcrisis, according to the Chief
OL,10,FInspector of Probation.
OL,12,FAn estimated 5,500 offenders are
OL,13,Fexpected to be released earlier than
OL,14,Fplanned in September and October under
OL,15,Fthe temporary move, which does not
OL,16,Fapply to those convicted of sex
OL,17,Foffences, terrorism, domestic abuse or
OL,18,Fsome violent offences.
