OL,3,CProbation chief warns 'things will go
OL,4,Cwrong' with early prison release scheme
OL,6,FHe said the implementation period has
OL,7,Fgiven the probation service "at least
OL,8,Fa fighting chance of getting this
OL,9,Fright", but the volume of offenders
OL,10,Fbeing released meant some could re-
OL,11,Foffend at a time when they would
OL,12,Fotherwise be in jail.
OL,14,FMr Jones told the newspaper: "I think
OL,15,Fit's inevitable, being realistic about
OL,16,Fit, that things will go wrong. I wish
OL,17,Fwe could live in a perfect world where
OL,18,Fthat doesn't happen.
